)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*:@@@A8@F@@@@* . THE @ASG'S ARE DONE IN TWO GROUPS: AN INITIAIY
)@@G@@L GROUP AND A MAIN:@@@B]@F@@@@* . GROUP.  THE INITIAL GROUP CAUSES THE FIZ
)@@G@@RONT PART OF THE FILE TO:@@@BG@G@@@@* . BE SPREAD OUT IN SMALLER INCREMEJA
)@@G@@NTS OVER A NUMBER OF DEVICES AND    :@@@BQ@F@@@@* . SUBSYSTEMS; THIS IS JB
)@@G@@DONE BECAUSE A HIGH PERCENTAGE OF MAPPER'S:@@@B)@F@@@@* . I/O IS DONE TOJC
)@@G@@ THIS PART OF THE FILE. THE MAIN GROUP ALLOCATES:@@@B%@G@@@@* . THE REMAJD
)@@G@@INDER OF THE FILE ACROSS ALL UNITS IN LARGER INCREMENTS.    :@@@B4@[@@@@JE
)@@G@@* .   :@@@B"@B@@@@* . FILSIZ HAS FOUR PARAMETRIC SUBFIELDS: :@@@CC@[@@@@JF
)@@G@@* .   :@@@CM@E@@@@* .   SUBFIELD 1: THE INITIAL RESERVE INCREMENT FOR THJG
)@@G@@E MAIN:@@@CW@A@@@@* .                  GROUP OF @ASG'S:@@@C&@A@@@@* .   JH
)@@G@@SUBFIELD 2: THE MAX TRACK SIZE:@@@C0@F@@@@* .   SUBFIELD 3: THE NUMBER OJI
)@@G@@F TRACKS IN THE INITIAL @ASG GROUP  :@@@C'@F@@@@* .   SUBFIELD 4: THE NUJJ
)@@G@@MBER OF DEVICES ONTO WHICH THE INITIAL    :@@@D^@D@@@@* .               JK
)@@G@@   @ASG GROUP IS TO BE ALLOCATED    :@@@DI@[@@@@* .   :@@@DS@F@@@@* . FIJL
)@@G@@ELD 6, SUBFIELD 1 ON THE DEVICE SGSES INDICATES THE TRACK   :@@@D+@F@@@@JM
)@@G@@* . AVAILABILITY ON THE DEVICE AT THE TIME THE CKMSALL WAS RUN.   :@@@D?JN
)@@G@@@F@@@@* . ALLOCATIONS AGAINST EACH DEVICE ARE DEDUCTED FROM THIS FIGURE,JO
)@@G@@:@@@D6@F@@@@* . AND THE DEVICE IS DROPPED FROM THE ALLOCATION ROTATION WJP
)@@G@@HEN   :@@@E@@F@@@@* . INSUFFICIENT SPACE REMAINS FOR FURTHER ALLOCATIONSJQ
)@@G@@.  AN ERROR :@@@EE@G@@@@* . TERMINATION COULD STILL RESULT IF THE SPACE JR
)@@G@@AVAILABILITY SHOULD     :@@@EO@F@@@@* . DECREASE SIGNIFICANTLY BETWEEN TJS
)@@G@@HE CKMSALL AND THE @ASG'S.    :@@@EY@[@@@@* .   :@@@E*@F@@@@* . ASGCNT IJT
)@@G@@S THE NUMBER OF @ASG IMAGES NEEDED IN THE MAIN GROUP  :@@@E2@G@@@@* . INJU
)@@G@@ITSIZ IS THE INITIAL RESERVE INCREMENT ON THE INITIAL @ASG IMAGES :@@@E/JV
)@@G@@@G@@@@* . INITRK IS THE SIZE OF INITIAL RESERVE ON THE CURRENT @ASG IMAGJW
)@@G@@E     :@@@FA@F@@@@* . THE DEVICE SGSES LIST THE CURRENT AVAILABLE UP'D DJX
)@@G@@ISK UNITS   :@@@FK@B@@@@* . J IS A POINTER INTO THE DEVICE LIST   :@@@FUJY
)@@G@@@H@@@@* . PASS NUMBER INDICATES HOW MANY TIMES WE'VE GONE THROUGH THE DEJZ
)@@G@@VICE LIST   :@@@F=@[@@@@*EJECT:@@@F,@#@@@@*DEFINE CHECKAVAIL:@@@F8@[@@@@KA
)@@G@@* .   :@@@G]@G@@@@* . ON EACH PASS THROUGH THE DEVICE LIST, THIS ROUTINEKB
)@@G@@ IS CALLED TO     :@@@GG@G@@@@* . VERIFY THAT THERE IS SUFFICIENT ROOM OKC
)@@G@@N EACH DEVICE TO ALLOCATE     :@@@GQ@G@@@@* . THE NEXT SEGMENT OF MAPER0KD
)@@G@@ ON THE DEVICE.  IF THERE IS INSUFFICIENT :@@@G)@G@@@@* . ROOM, THE DEVIKE
)@@G@@CE IS REMOVED FROM THE LIST AND A MESSAGE DISPLAYED.  :@@@G%@[@@@@* .   KF
)@@G@@:@@@G4@F@@@@* . INPUT PARAMETER: SIZE (INCREMENT) OF NEXT ALLOCATION SEGKG
)@@G@@MENT  :@@@G"@[@@@@* .   :@@@HC@D@@@@*SET PASS TO PASS+1                 KH
)@@G@@   . BUMP PASS #  :@@@HM@F@@@@*INCREMENT I FROM [DEVICE] TO 1 BY -1  . TKI
)@@G@@HROUGH THE DEVICE LIST  :@@@HW@D@[@@*IF +[DEVICE,I,6,2] > +[#1]  . AVAILKJ
)@@G@@ABILITY > NEEDED? @D@]@[*IF +[DEVICE,I,3,1] > +[#1]  . AVAILABILITY > NEKK
)@@G@@EDED? @D@#@]*IF +[DEVICE,I,4,1] > +[#1]  . AVAILABILITY > NEEDED? @D@@@#KL

)@@G@@@F@@@T* . GROUP.  THE INITIAL GROUP CAUSES THE FRONT PART OF THE FILE TONP

)@@G@@ENTAGE OF MAPPER'S:@@@B)@F@@@T* . I/O IS DONE TO THIS PART OF THE FILE. NS

)@@G@@ ALL UNITS IN LARGER INCREMENTS.    :@@@B4@[@@@T* .   :@@@B"@B@@@T* . FINU

)@@G@@LLOCATED    :@@@DI@[@@@T* .   :@@@DS@F@U@T* . FIELD 6, SUBFIELD 1 ON THEOB

)@@G@@DEVICE AT THE TIME THE CKMSALL WAS RUN.   :@@@D?@F@@@T* . ALLOCATIONS AGOE
)@@G@@AINST EACH DEVICE ARE DEDUCTED FROM THIS FIGURE,:@@@D6@F@@@T* . AND THE OF

)@@G@@SUFFICIENT SPACE REMAINS FOR FURTHER ALLOCATIONS.  AN ERROR :@@@EE@G@@@TOH

)@@G@@        .   @B@@@Q          E$COL     65                .   @E@@@Q      SA
)@@G@@    E$MSG     PER               . DONE WITH TOP LINE  @F@@@Q          P$SB
)@@G@@RINT    (PFX 1,13,HDG)     . PRINT TOP LINE OF HEADING@F@@@Q          E$SC
)@@G@@CLEAR                     . CLEAR HDG BUFFER TO SPACES@E@@@Q          E$SD
)@@G@@MSG     NAM               . START CREATING LOWER@F@@@Q          E$COL   SE
)@@G@@  8                . LINE. POSITION AT COLUMN 14@B@@@Q          E$MSG   SF
)@@G@@  EL                .   @B@@@Q          E$COL     20                .   SG
)@@G@@@B@@@Q          E$MSG     TRK               .   @B@@@Q          E$COL   SH
)@@G@@  33                .   @B@@@Q          E$MSG     ALOC              .   SI
)@@G@@@B@@@Q          E$COL     45                .   @B@@@Q          E$MSG   SJ
)@@G@@  RE                .   @B@@@Q          E$COL     55                .   SK
)@@G@@@B@@@Q          E$MSG     GRA               .   @B@@@Q          E$COL   SL
)@@G@@  65                .   @E@@@Q          E$MSG     INU               . DOSM
)@@G@@NE WITH LOWER LINE@G@@@Q          P$RINT    (PFX 1,13,HDG)     . PRINT LSN
)@@G@@OWER LINE OF HEADING    @D@@@Q          P$RINT    (PFX 1,13,STARS)   . PSO
)@@G@@RINT DIVIDER@F@@@Q          LX        X4,(2,0)          . SET UP INDEX TSP
)@@G@@O FILE NAMES@E@@@Q          DEC       LOOPCTL           . SET UP FOR LOOSQ
)@@G@@P     @B@@@Q          NOP                         .   @D@@@Q          LRSR
)@@G@@        R3,LOOPCTL        . SET FOR JGD   @F@@@QLOOP      SZ        FLAGSS
)@@G@@              . CLEAR FLAG FOR THIS FILE  @D@@@Q          DL        A0,AST
)@@G@@FTBL,X4        . GET FILE NAME@G@@@Q          DS        A0,FCT          SU
)@@G@@  . STORE FILE NAME IN FCT PACKET   @G@@@Q          DS        A0,FPKT   SV
)@@G@@        . STORE FILE NAME IN FITEM PACKET @E@@@Q          LA,U      A0,FSW
)@@G@@CT            . SET UP A0 FOR RFTI$ @F@@@Q          LMJ       X11,RFTI$ SX
)@@G@@        . GO READ FILE TABLE INDEX  @D@@@Q          NOP                 SY
)@@G@@        . ERROR RETURN  @D@@@Q          TNE,U     A0,2              . CHSZ
)@@G@@ECK STATUS  @H@@@Q          J         NPF               . NOT A PROGRAM TA
)@@G@@FILE GO INFORM XQT'ER   @E@@@Q          TP        A0                . SOTB
)@@G@@ME I/O STATUS ?   @E@@@Q          J         IOE               . YES GO ITC
)@@G@@NFORM XQT'ER@F@@@Q          LA        A1,PF             . NO - GET PROGRTD
)@@G@@AM FILE WORD@E@@@Q          TE        A1,FCT+6          . MAKE SURE WE'RTE
)@@G@@E OK  @F@@@Q          J         PFE               . OOPS NOT OK GO TELL TF
)@@G@@XQT'ER@[@@@Q.     @B@@@Q. CALCULATE NUMBER OF ELEMENTS IN THE FILE@C@@@QTG
)@@G@@. SINCE IT'S A MAPPER FILE WE HAVE NO DELETED   @C@@@Q. ELEMENTS. THEY STH
)@@G@@HOULD ALSO ALL BE SYMBOLICS.  @[@@@Q.     @F@@@Q          E$CLEAR       TI
)@@G@@              . CLEAR HDG BUFFER TO SPACES@G@@@Q          E$FD2     AFTBTJ
)@@G@@L,*X4          . GET FILE NAME AND INC. POINTER @B@@@Q          E$COL   TK
)@@G@@  8                .    @I@@@Q          LA,H1     A1,FCT+10         . RFTL
)@@G@@TI$ WENT OK - GET ELEMENT TABLE LENGTH    @E@@@Q          SZ        A0  TM
)@@G@@              . SET UP FOR DIVIDE   @G@@@Q          AN,U      A1,140    TN
)@@G@@        . SUBTRACT POINTER TABLE LENGTH   @G@@@Q          DI,U      A0,1TO
)@@G@@0             . DIVIDE BY ELEMENT TABLE LENGTH  @F@@@Q          TZ      TP
)@@G@@  A1                . SHOULD HAVE BEEN EVEN     @F@@@Q          LMJ     TQ
)@@G@@  X11,UNEVEN        . NOT EVEN GO TELL XQT'ER   @H@@@Q          TG,U    TR
)@@G@@  A0,3499           . DOES THIS FILE EXCEED 3500 ELEMENTS ? @E@@@Q      TS
)@@G@@    SP1       FLAG              . YES SO SET FLAG     @F@@@Q          AUTT
)@@G@@        A0,RIDTOT         . ACCUMULATE TOTAL NUMBER OF@G@@@Q          SATU
)@@G@@        A1,RIDTOT         . ELEMENTS FOR ALL FILE COMBINED  @E@@@Q      TV
)@@G@@    LA,U      A1,7              . GIVE EDIT FIELD SIZE@F@@@Q          LMTW
)@@G@@J       X11,EDECF$        . A0 HAS VALUE SO DO LMJ    @B@@@Q          E$TX
)@@G@@COL     20                .   @[@@@Q.     @B@@@Q. CALCULATE NEXT TRACK TTY
)@@G@@O BE WRITTEN TO   @D@@@Q. ROUNDED UP, WE START WITH NEXT SECTOR AVAILABLTZ
)@@G@@E     @^@@@Q. FOR WRITING TEXT.     @[@@@Q.     @H@@@Q          LA      UA
)@@G@@  A1,FCT+7          . GET NEXT SECTOR AVAIL. FOR WRITING    @E@@@Q      UB
)@@G@@    SZ        A0                . SET UP A0 FOR DIVIDE@F@@@Q          DIUC
)@@G@@,U      A0,64             . DIVIDE BY SECTORS/TRACK   @D@@@Q          TZUD
)@@G@@        A1                . EVEN DIVIDE?  @D@@@Q          AA,U      A0,1UE
)@@G@@              . NO - ROUND UP @F@@@Q          AU        A0,TRKTOT       UF
)@@G@@  . ACCUMULATE TOTAL NUMBER OF@D@@@Q          SA        A1,TRKTOT       UG
)@@G@@  . TRACKS IN USE.@H@@@Q          SA        A0,A5             . ****** SUH
)@@G@@AVE FOR LATTER USE ******     @E@@@Q          LA,U      A1,8            UI
)@@G@@  . GIVE EDIT FIELD SIZE@F@@@Q          LMJ       X11,EDECF$        . A0UJ
)@@G@@ HAS VALUE SO DO LMJ    @B@@@Q          E$COL     33                .   UK
)@@G@@@[@@@Q.     @C@@@Q. GET HIGHEST TRACK ALLOCATED VIA ER FITEM$     @E@@@QUL
)@@G@@          LA        A0,(13,FPKT)      . SET UP A0 FOR ER    @C@@@Q      UM
)@@G@@    ER        FITEM$            . DO IT   @E@@@Q          SSL       A0,3UN
)@@G@@0             . SHIFT OVER STAUTS   @F@@@Q          JNZ       A0,FITEME UO
)@@G@@        . ERROR GO TO FITEME ELSE NI@I@@@Q          LA,H2     A0,FPKT+9 UP
)@@G@@        . YES - GET HIGHEST GRANULE NUMBER ASSIGNED   @E@@@Q          LAUQ
)@@G@@,U      A1,7              . GIVE EDIT FIELD SIZE@F@@@Q          LMJ     UR
)@@G@@  X11,EDECF$        . A0 HAS VALUE SO DO LMJ    @^@@@Q          E$COL   US
)@@G@@  45  @F@@@Q          LA,H1     A0,FPKT+8         . INITIAL GRANULE COUNUT
)@@G@@T     @E@@@Q          LA,U      A1,5              . GIVE EDIT FIELD SIZEUU
)@@G@@@C@@@Q          LMJ       X11,EDECF$        . EDIT IT @^@@@Q          E$UV
)@@G@@COL     55  @E@@@Q          LA,H2     A0,FPKT+8         . MAX. GRANULE CUW
)@@G@@OUNT  @F@@@Q          SZ        A4                . SET UP FOR DIVIDE OFUX
)@@G@@ A5   @G@@@Q          MSI,U     A5,100            . SET UP FOR PERCENTAGUY
)@@G@@E CALC.     @C@@@Q          DI        A4,A0             . DO IT   @H@@@QUZ
)@@G@@          TG,U      A4,90             . DID THIS FILE EXCEED 90% OF ITS VA
)@@G@@MAX.? @E@@@Q          SP1       FLAG              . YES SO SET FLAG     VB
)@@G@@@E@@@Q          LA,U      A1,6              . GIVE EDIT FIELD SIZE@C@@@QVC
)@@G@@          LMJ       X11,EDECF$        . EDIT IT @B@@@Q          E$COL   VD
)@@G@@  65                .   @E@@@Q          LA,U      A1,8             . GIVVE
)@@G@@E EDIT$ FIELD SIZE@E@@@Q          LA        A0,A4             . BRING OVVF
)@@G@@ER PERCENT  @B@@@Q          LMJ       X11,EDECF$        .   @K@@@Q      VG
)@@G@@    TZ        FLAG              . DID THIS FILE EXCEED ELEMENT OR % OF TVH
)@@G@@RACKS IN USE LIMIT@F@@@Q          LMJ       X10,FLAGIT        . YES GO FVI
)@@G@@LAG FILE NAME     @A@@@Q          P$RINT    (PFX 1,13,HDG)  @E@@@Q      VJ
)@@G@@    JGD       R3,LOOP           . GO DO NEXT FILE     @B@@@Q          P$VK
)@@G@@RINT    (PFX 1,13,STARS)   .  @B@@@Q          E$CLEAR                   VL
)@@G@@  .   @F@@@Q          E$MSG     TOTR              . INSERT TOTAL LINE MEVM
)@@G@@SSAGE @E@@@Q          E$COLN                      . GET COLUMN NUMBER   VN
)@@G@@@H@@@Q          SA        A0,COL            . SAVE COLUMN POSITION FOR NVO
)@@G@@EXT TOTAL   @D@@@Q          E$COL     4,A0              . LEAVE 4 SPACESVP
)@@G@@@D@@@Q          LA        A0,RIDTOT         . GET THE NUMBER@D@@@Q      VQ
)@@G@@    E$DECF                      . PUT IN NUMBER @A@@@Q          P$RINT  VR
)@@G@@  (PFX 2,13,HDG)  @B@@@Q          E$CLEAR                     .   @F@@@QVS
)@@G@@          E$MSG     TOTT              . INSERT TOTAL LINE MESSAGE @E@@@QVT
)@@G@@          LA        A0,COL            . KEEP TOTALS IN LINE @D@@@Q      VU
)@@G@@    E$COL     4,A0              . LEAVE 4 SPACES@D@@@Q          LA      VV
)@@G@@  A0,TRKTOT         . GET THE NUMBER@D@@@Q          E$DECF              VW
)@@G@@        . PUT IN NUMBER @A@@@Q          P$RINT    (PFX 1,13,HDG)  @B@@@QVX
)@@G@@          E$CLEAR                     .   @D@@@Q          E$MSG     FLG VY
)@@G@@              . GET MESSAGE   @A@@@Q          P$RINT    (PFX 3,13,HDG)  VZ
)@@G@@@ @@@Q          ER        EXIT$     @G@@@QFLAGIT    E$COL     6         WA
)@@G@@        . THIS CODE IS DEPENDANT ON THE   @E@@@Q          LA        A0,SWB
)@@G@@TARS          . FILE NAME BEING ONLY@F@@@Q          LMJ       X11,ECHAR$WC
)@@G@@        . 6 CHARACTERS IN LENGTH !  @C@@@Q          J         0,X10     WD
)@@G@@        . RETURN  @B@@@QUNEVEN    L$SNAP    'UNEVEN',7,34,FCT     @H@@@QWE
)@@G@@          J         0,X11             . GO BACK AND CONTINUE WITH SAME FWF
)@@G@@ILE   @B@@@QNPF       E$CLEAR                     .   @E@@@Q          E$WG
)@@G@@MSG     NPFM              . INSERT ERROR MESSAGE@D@@@Q          P$RINT  WH
)@@G@@  (PFX 1,13,HDG)     . PRINT MESSAGE@E@@@Q          NOP       ,,*X4     WI
)@@G@@        . BUMP FILE POINTER   @H@@@Q          JGD       R3,LOOP         WJ
)@@G@@  . SKIP REST OF THIS FILE GO TO NEXT ONE @E@@@QIOE       SA,S6     A0,IWK
)@@G@@OS            . STORE I/O STATUS    @B@@@Q          E$CLEAR             WL
)@@G@@        .   @E@@@Q          E$MSG     IOEM              . INSERT ERROR MWM
)@@G@@ESSAGE@B@@@Q          E$COL     15                .   @D@@@Q          E$WN
)@@G@@DECF    IOS               . GET I/O STATUS@D@@@Q          P$RINT    (PFXWO
)@@G@@ 1,13,HDG)     . PRINT MESSAGE@E@@@Q          NOP       ,,*X4           WP
)@@G@@  . BUMP FILE POINTER   @H@@@Q          JGD       R3,LOOP           . SKWQ
)@@G@@IP REST OF THIS FILE GO TO NEXT ONE @B@@@QPFE       E$CLEAR             WR
)@@G@@        .   @E@@@Q          E$MSG     PFEM              . INSERT ERROR MWS
)@@G@@ESSAGE@D@@@Q          P$RINT    (PFX 1,13,HDG)     . PRINT MESSAGE@C@@@QWT
)@@G@@          L$SNAP    'PFE',7,34,FCT    . SNAP FCT@E@@@Q          NOP     WU
)@@G@@  ,,*X4             . BUMP FILE POINTER   @H@@@Q          JGD       R3,LWV
)@@G@@OOP           . SKIP REST OF THIS FILE GO TO NEXT ONE @E@@@QFITEME    SAWW
)@@G@@,S1     A0,FITEMS         . STORE FITEM STATUS  @E@@@Q          E$MSG   WX
)@@G@@  FITEMM            . INSERT ERROR MESSAGE@B@@@Q          E$COL     75  WY
)@@G@@              .   @E@@@Q          E$DECF    FITEMS            . GET FITEWZ
)@@G@@M STATUS    @D@@@Q          P$RINT    (PFX 1,13,HDG)     . PRINT MESSAGEXA
)@@G@@@E@@@Q          NOP       ,,*X4             . BUMP FILE POINTER   @H@@@QXB
)@@G@@          JGD       R3,LOOP           . SKIP REST OF THIS FILE GO TO NEXXC
)@@G@@T ONE @[@@@QCSFERR@B@R@Q          DEC       R2                .   @^@R@QXD
)@@G@@          NOP       .   @B@@@Q          DL        A0,MAP1,*X4       .   XE
)@@G@@@G@@@Q          DS        A0,UFTBL,*X6      . STORE IN UNASSIGNED FILE LXF
)@@G@@IST   @B@R@Q          J         FILE              .   @B@@@R          JGXG
)@@G@@D       R2,FILE           .   @J@@@T          J         LASTF           XH
)@@G@@  . IF CSF FOR LAST FILE FAILS THIS JUMP IS TAKEN     @^@@@Q          ENXI
)@@G@@D       ST  _@@@@@  .  R)@@[S@@@@@@@HIGHESITE & FOR WRRACK &NEXT TTS &  XJ
)@@G@@ELEMEN OF & NUMBERNAME &FILE &AA@@@@)@F[S@@@@@@@ES &  GRANULM &   MAXIMUXK
)@@G@@E &   RESERVL &   INITIATED & ALLOCAT &   AB@@@@)@Q[S@@@@@@@TRACKSTOTAL XL

)@@G@@AGE   :@@@B%@^@@@@IOEM      'I/O ERROR &' :@@@B4@D@@@@IOS       +       NZ

)@@G@@  $-PFEM            . LENGTH OF MESSAGE   :@@@CW@A@@@@FITEMM    'BAD ER OD
)@@G@@FITEM$ STATUS &'  :@@@C&@E@@@@FITEMS    +         0                 . STOE

)@@G@@        . TOTAL NUMBER OF TRACKS IN USE   :@@@DI@B@@@@FLAG      +       OI
)@@G@@  0                 .   :@@@DS@F@@@@COL       +         0               OJ

)@@G@@        . SAVE LOCATION FOR DATE AND TIME :@@@D?@ @@@@PF        $FORM   OL
)@@G@@  12,6,18   :@@@D6@]@@@@$(1),ST     :@@@E@@F@@@@          E$DIT     EDPKOM
)@@G@@T             . INITILIZE EDIT$ PACKAGE   :@@@EE@F@@@@          E$CLEAR ON
)@@G@@                    . CLEAR HDG BUFFER TO SPACES:@@@EO@E@@@@          EROO
)@@G@@        TDATE$            . GET TIME AND DATE   :@@@EY@E@@@@          SAOP
)@@G@@        A0,DATIM          . SAVE DATE AND TIME  :@@@E*@D@@@@          LMOQ
)@@G@@J       X11,EDAY1$        . EDIT DATE     :@@@E2@B@@@@          E$SKIP  OR
)@@G@@  4                 .   :@@@E/@D@@@@          LA        A0,DATIM        OS
)@@G@@  .  RESTORE A0   :@@@FA@D@@@@          LMJ       X11,ETIME$        . EDOT
)@@G@@IT TIME     :@@@FK@A@@@@          P$RINT    (PF 1,13,HDG)   :@@@FU@B@@@@OU
)@@G@@          E$CLEAR                     .   :@@@F=@B@@@@          E$MSG   OV
)@@G@@  FN                .   :@@@F,@E@@@@          E$COL     8               OW
)@@G@@ . POSITION AT COLUMN 14:@@@F8@D@@@@          E$MSG     NEL             OX
)@@G@@  . START CREATING:@@@G]@D@@@@          E$COL     20                . OFOY

)@@G@@@B@@@@          E$COL     33                .   :@@@G)@B@@@@          E$PA
)@@G@@MSG     HIGH              .   :@@@G%@B@@@@          E$COL     45        PB

)@@G@@        .   :@@@HW@E@@@@          E$MSG     PER               . DONE WITPF

)@@G@@@E@@@@          E$MSG     INU               . DONE WITH LOWER LINE:@@@J/PS
)@@G@@@G@@@@          P$RINT    (PF 1,13,HDG)     . PRINT LOWER LINE OF HEADINPT
)@@G@@G     :@@@KA@D@@@@          P$RINT    (PF 1,13,STARS)   . PRINT DIVIDER PU
)@@G@@:@@@KF@F@@@@          LR,U      R2,36             . SET UP TO LOOP 36 TIPV
)@@G@@MES   :@@@KK@[@@@@LOOP. :@@@KL@D@@@@          L,S6      A0,FPKT         PW
)@@G@@   . GET FILENAME :@@@KM@D@@@@          A,U       A0,1               . BPX
)@@G@@UMP TO NEXT :@@@KN@G@@@@          TNE,U     A0,072             . DID WE PY
)@@G@@HIT END OF NUMBERS?     :@@@KO@F@@@@          L,U       A0,'A'          PZ
)@@G@@   . YES, THEN START LETTERS  :@@@KP@F@@@@          S,S6      A0,FPKT   QA
)@@G@@         . BACK TO FITEM$ PACKET    :@@@K=@F@@@@          SZ        FLAGQB
)@@G@@              . CLEAR FLAG FOR THIS FILE  :@@@K8@G@@@@          S,S6    QC
)@@G@@  A0,FCT            . STORE FILE NAME IN FCT PACKET   :@@@K9@E@@@@      QD
)@@G@@    LA        A0,(13,FPKT)      . SET UP A0 FOR ER    :@@@K'@C@@@@      QE
)@@G@@    ER        FITEM$            . DO IT   :@@@K;@D@@@@          TNZ,S1  QF
)@@G@@  FPKT+6             . ASSIGNED?    :@@@K/@F@@@@          J         END QG
)@@G@@               . NO - MUST BE END OF LIST :@@@LG@E@@@@          LA,U    QH
)@@G@@  A0,FCT            . SET UP A0 FOR RFTI$ :@@@LQ@F@@@@          LMJ     QI
)@@G@@  X11,RFTI$         . GO READ FILE TABLE INDEX  :@@@L)@D@@@@          NOQJ
)@@G@@P                         . ERROR RETURN  :@@@L%@D@@@@          TNE,U   QK
)@@G@@  A0,2              . CHECK STATUS  :@@@L4@H@@@@          J         NPF QL
)@@G@@              . NOT A PROGRAM FILE GO INFORM XQT'ER   :@@@L"@E@@@@      QM
)@@G@@    TP        A0                . SOME I/O STATUS ?   :@@@MC@E@@@@      QN
)@@G@@    J         IOE               . YES GO INFORM XQT'ER:@@@MM@F@@@@      QO
)@@G@@    LA        A1,PF             . NO - GET PROGRAM FILE WORD:@@@MW@E@@@@QP
)@@G@@          TE        A1,FCT+6          . MAKE SURE WE'RE OK  :@@@M&@F@@@@QQ
)@@G@@          J         PFE               . OOPS NOT OK GO TELL XQT'ER:@@@M0QR
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     :@@@M'@B@@@@. CALCULATE NUMBER OF ELEMENTS IN THE FILE:@@@N^QS
)@@G@@@C@@@@. SINCE IT'S A MAPPER FILE WE HAVE NO DELETED   :@@@NI@C@@@@. ELEMQT
)@@G@@ENTS. THEY SHOULD ALSO ALL BE SYMBOLICS.  :@@@NS@[@@@@.     :@@@N+@F@@@@QU
)@@G@@          E$CLEAR                     . CLEAR HDG BUFFER TO SPACES:@@@N?QV
)@@G@@@G@@@@          E$FD2     FPKT              . GET FILE NAME AND INC. POIQW
)@@G@@NTER  :@@@N6@B@@@@          E$COL     8                .    :@@@O@@I@@@@QX
)@@G@@          LA,H1     A1,FCT+10         . RFTI$ WENT OK - GET ELEMENT TABLQY
)@@G@@E LENGTH    :@@@OE@E@@@@          SZ        A0                . SET UP FQZ
)@@G@@OR DIVIDE   :@@@OO@G@@@@          AN,U      A1,140            . SUBTRACTRA
)@@G@@ POINTER TABLE LENGTH   :@@@OY@G@@@@          DI,U      A0,10           RB
)@@G@@  . DIVIDE BY ELEMENT TABLE LENGTH  :@@@O*@F@@@@          TZ        A1  RC
)@@G@@              . SHOULD HAVE BEEN EVEN     :@@@O2@F@@@@          LMJ     RD
)@@G@@  X11,UNEVEN        . NOT EVEN GO TELL XQT'ER   :@@@O/@H@@@@          TGRE
)@@G@@,U      A0,3499           . DOES THIS FILE EXCEED 3500 ELEMENTS ? :@@@PARF
)@@G@@@E@@@@          SP1       FLAG              . YES SO SET FLAG     :@@@PKRG
)@@G@@@F@@@@          AU        A0,RIDTOT         . ACCUMULATE TOTAL NUMBER OFRH
)@@G@@:@@@PU@G@@@@          SA        A1,RIDTOT         . ELEMENTS FOR ALL FILRI
)@@G@@E COMBINED  :@@@P=@E@@@@          LA,U      A1,7              . GIVE EDIRJ
)@@G@@T FIELD SIZE:@@@P,@F@@@@          LMJ       X11,EDECF$        . A0 HAS VRK
)@@G@@ALUE SO DO LMJ    :@@@P8@B@@@@          E$COL     20                .   RL
)@@G@@:@@@Q]@[@@@@.     :@@@QG@B@@@@. CALCULATE NEXT TRACK TO BE WRITTEN TO   RM
)@@G@@:@@@QQ@D@@@@. ROUNDED UP, WE START WITH NEXT SECTOR AVAILABLE     :@@@Q)RN
)@@G@@@^@@@@. FOR WRITING TEXT.     :@@@Q%@[@@@@.     :@@@Q4@H@@@@          LARO
)@@G@@        A1,FCT+7          . GET NEXT SECTOR AVAIL. FOR WRITING    :@@@Q"RP
)@@G@@@E@@@@          SZ        A0                . SET UP A0 FOR DIVIDE:@@@RCRQ
)@@G@@@F@@@@          DI,U      A0,64             . DIVIDE BY SECTORS/TRACK   RR
)@@G@@:@@@RM@D@@@@          TZ        A1                . EVEN DIVIDE?  :@@@RWRS
)@@G@@@D@@@@          AA,U      A0,1              . NO - ROUND UP :@@@R&@F@@@@RT
)@@G@@          AU        A0,TRKTOT         . ACCUMULATE TOTAL NUMBER OF:@@@R0RU
)@@G@@@D@@@@          SA        A1,TRKTOT         . TRACKS IN USE.:@@@R'@H@@@@RV
)@@G@@          SA        A0,A5             . ****** SAVE FOR LATTER USE *****RW
)@@G@@*     :@@@S^@E@@@@          LA,U      A1,8              . GIVE EDIT FIELRX
)@@G@@D SIZE:@@@SI@F@@@@          LMJ       X11,EDECF$        . A0 HAS VALUE SRY
)@@G@@O DO LMJ    :@@@SS@B@@@@          E$COL     33                .   :@@@S+RZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     :@@@S?@C@@@@. GET HIGHEST TRACK ALLOCATED VIA ER FITEM$     SA
)@@G@@:@@@TY@I@@@@          LA,H2     A0,FPKT+9         . YES - GET HIGHEST GRSB
)@@G@@ANULE NUMBER ASSIGNED   :@@@T*@E@@@@          LA,U      A1,7            SC
)@@G@@  . GIVE EDIT FIELD SIZE:@@@T2@F@@@@          LMJ       X11,EDECF$      SD
)@@G@@  . A0 HAS VALUE SO DO LMJ    :@@@T/@^@@@@          E$COL     45  :@@@UASE
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA,H1     A0,FPKT+8         . INITIAL GRANULE COUNT     SF
)@@G@@:@@@UK@E@@@@          LA,U      A1,5              . GIVE EDIT FIELD SIZESG
)@@G@@:@@@UU@C@@@@          LMJ       X11,EDECF$        . EDIT IT :@@@U=@^@@@@SH
)@@G@@          E$COL     55  :@@@U,@E@@@@          LA,H2     A0,FPKT+8       SI
)@@G@@  . MAX. GRANULE COUNT  :@@@U8@F@@@@          SZ        A4              SJ
)@@G@@  . SET UP FOR DIVIDE OF A5   :@@@V]@G@@@@          MSI,U     A5,100    SK
)@@G@@        . SET UP FOR PERCENTAGE CALC.     :@@@VG@C@@@@          DI      SL
)@@G@@  A4,A0             . DO IT   :@@@VQ@H@@@@          TG,U      A4,89     SM
)@@G@@        . DID THIS FILE EXCEED 90% OF ITS MAX.? :@@@V)@E@@@@          SPSN
)@@G@@1       FLAG              . YES SO SET FLAG     :@@@V%@E@@@@          LASO
)@@G@@,U      A1,6              . GIVE EDIT FIELD SIZE:@@@V4@C@@@@          LMSP
)@@G@@J       X11,EDECF$        . EDIT IT :@@@V"@B@@@@          E$COL     65  SQ
)@@G@@              .   :@@@WC@E@@@@          LA,U      A1,8             . GIVSR
)@@G@@E EDIT$ FIELD SIZE:@@@WM@E@@@@          LA        A0,A4             . BRSS
)@@G@@ING OVER PERCENT  :@@@WW@B@@@@          LMJ       X11,EDECF$        .   ST
)@@G@@:@@@W&@K@@@@          TZ        FLAG              . DID THIS FILE EXCEEDSU
)@@G@@ ELEMENT OR % OF TRACKS IN USE LIMIT:@@@W0@F@@@@          LMJ       X10,SV
)@@G@@FLAGIT        . YES GO FLAG FILE NAME     :@@@W'@A@@@@          P$RINT  SW
)@@G@@  (PF 1,13,HDG)   :@@@X^@E@@@@          JGD       R2,LOOP           . GOSX
)@@G@@ DO NEXT FILE     :@@@XI@B@@@@END       P$RINT    (PF 1,13,STARS)   .   SY
)@@G@@:@@@XS@B@@@@          E$CLEAR                     .   :@@@X+@F@@@@      SZ
)@@G@@    E$MSG     TOTR              . INSERT TOTAL LINE MESSAGE :@@@X?@E@@@@TA
)@@G@@          E$COLN                      . GET COLUMN NUMBER   :@@@X6@H@@@@TB
)@@G@@          SA        A0,COL            . SAVE COLUMN POSITION FOR NEXT TOTC
)@@G@@TAL   :@@@Y@@D@@@@          E$COL     4,A0              . LEAVE 4 SPACESTD
)@@G@@:@@@YE@D@@@@          LA        A0,RIDTOT         . GET THE NUMBER:@@@YOTE
)@@G@@@D@@@@          E$DECF                      . PUT IN NUMBER :@@@YY@A@@@@TF
)@@G@@          P$RINT    (PF 2,13,HDG)   :@@@Y*@B@@@@          E$CLEAR       TG
)@@G@@              .   :@@@Y2@F@@@@          E$MSG     TOTT              . INTH
)@@G@@SERT TOTAL LINE MESSAGE :@@@Y/@E@@@@          LA        A0,COL          TI
)@@G@@  . KEEP TOTALS IN LINE :@@@ZA@D@@@@          E$COL     4,A0            TJ
)@@G@@  . LEAVE 4 SPACES:@@@ZK@D@@@@          LA        A0,TRKTOT         . GETK
)@@G@@T THE NUMBER:@@@ZU@D@@@@          E$DECF                      . PUT IN NTL
)@@G@@UMBER :@@@Z=@A@@@@          P$RINT    (PF 1,13,HDG)   :@@@Z,@B@@@@      TM
)@@G@@    E$CLEAR                     .   :@@@Z8@D@@@@          E$MSG     FLG TN
)@@G@@              . GET MESSAGE   :@@@)]@A@@@@          P$RINT    (PF 3,13,HTO
)@@G@@DG)   :@@@)G@ @@@@          ER        EXIT$     :@@@)Q@G@@@@FLAGIT    E$TP
)@@G@@COL     6                 . THIS CODE IS DEPENDANT ON THE   :@@@))@E@@@@TQ
)@@G@@          LA        A0,STARS          . FILE NAME BEING ONLY:@@@)%@F@@@@TR
)@@G@@          LMJ       X11,ECHAR$        . 6 CHARACTERS IN LENGTH !  :@@@)4TS
)@@G@@@C@@@@          J         0,X10             . RETURN  :@@@)"@B@@@@UNEVENTT
)@@G@@    L$SNAP    'UNEVEN',7,34,FCT     :@@@-C@H@@@@          J         0,X1TU
)@@G@@1             . GO BACK AND CONTINUE WITH SAME FILE   :@@@-M@B@@@@NPF   TV
)@@G@@    E$CLEAR                     .   :@@@-W@E@@@@          E$MSG     NPFMTW
)@@G@@              . INSERT ERROR MESSAGE:@@@-&@D@@@@          P$RINT    (PF TX
)@@G@@1,13,HDG)     . PRINT MESSAGE :@@@-'@H@@@@          JGD       R2,LOOP   TY
)@@G@@        . SKIP REST OF THIS FILE GO TO NEXT ONE :@@@+^@E@@@@IOE       SATZ
)@@G@@,S6     A0,IOS            . STORE I/O STATUS    :@@@+I@B@@@@          E$UA
)@@G@@CLEAR                     .   :@@@+S@E@@@@          E$MSG     IOEM      UB
)@@G@@        . INSERT ERROR MESSAGE:@@@++@B@@@@          E$COL     15        UC
)@@G@@        .   :@@@+?@D@@@@          E$DECF    IOS               . GET I/O UD
)@@G@@STATUS:@@@+6@D@@@@          P$RINT    (PF 1,13,HDG)     . PRINT MESSAGE UE
)@@G@@:@@@<E@H@@@@          JGD       R2,LOOP           . SKIP REST OF THIS FIUF
)@@G@@LE GO TO NEXT ONE :@@@<O@B@@@@PFE       E$CLEAR                     .   UG
)@@G@@:@@@<Y@E@@@@          E$MSG     PFEM              . INSERT ERROR MESSAGEUH
)@@G@@:@@@<*@D@@@@          P$RINT    (PF 1,13,HDG)     . PRINT MESSAGE :@@@<2UI
)@@G@@@C@@@@          L$SNAP    'PFE',7,34,FCT    . SNAP FCT:@@@=A@H@@@@      UJ

)@@G@@@[@@@@@EOF .@#@@@@@PACK MAPER1.     @#@@@@@PRT,TL MAPER1.   ___DDO@[[@[@XC
)@@G@@C[ D9A@]@@[@C[ D9A^@,^@)*[@@@@*SDFF*@@@@@@@H@@@@                        XD
)@@G@@   UTILITIES                 10 MINUTE PRESENTATION   @@@@@@@[@@@@(1) MTXE
)@@G@@@]@@@@(2) MUDDLE  @]@@@@(3) READ-RID@#@@@@(4) WRITE-RID     @#@@@@(5) REXF
)@@G@@AD-MAPPER   @@@@@@@@@@@@@I@@@@PART 1 -  MUDDLE & MT.                    XG
)@@G@@                           (5 MINUTES)))))@@@@@@@I@@@@REASON FOR USE - NXH
)@@G@@EED TO BE ABLE TO MOVE TYPES FROM ONE HISTORY FILE TO ANOTHER     @H@@@@XI
)@@G@@                 AVOIDING 'SYSENT' PROBLEMS IF A LARGE NUMBER OF RIDS EXXJ
)@@G@@IST   @I@@@@                 IN ONE TYPE IN A MAPER'N' FILE CONTAINING MXK
)@@G@@ULTIPLE OCTAL TYPES.....@@@@@@@G@@@@'MT' -           WORKS WITHIN MAPPERXL
)@@G@@; A MASK REQUESTS THE OCTAL TYPE AND@H@@@@                 DESTINATION FXM
)@@G@@ILE NUMBER.  THE NEXT PURGE ACTUALLY MOVES THE  @H@@@@                 DXN
)@@G@@ATA FOR YOU. THE COORDINATOR SHOULD CREATE AN ENTRY IN THE  @H@@@@      XO
)@@G@@           PURGE INDEX RID FOR THE NEW FILE BEFORE PURGE OR CYCLE. THIS XP
)@@G@@@I@@@@                 FUNCTION MOVES AN ENTIRE TYPE WITHOUT CHANGING THXQ
)@@G@@E OCTAL TYPE,     @G@@@@                 JUST THE MAPER'N' FILE THAT THEXR
)@@G@@ DATA RESIDES WITHIN.   @@@@@@@I@@@@REQUIREMENTS -   ADDITIONAL CODE IN XS
)@@G@@MAPPER ELEMENTS 'PREFUN','REPCON','MAPROC'.     @I@@@@                 AXT
)@@G@@N ADDITIONAL FUNCTION MASK IN MODE 218 TYPE C MUST BE SUPPLIEDDDDD@I@@@@XU
)@@G@@                 FOR INPUT TO THE FUNCTION. A USER STOP BIT IS AVAILABLEXV
)@@G@@ TO STOPPPPP@H@@@@                 THE USE OF THE FUNCTION. THIS OPERATIXW
)@@G@@ON MAY BE USED IN EITHER@I@@@@                 PURGE OR MERGE, BUT IT ISXX
)@@G@@ SAFER TO USE THE PURGE PROCESS RATHERRRRR@D@@@@                 THAN MEXY
)@@G@@RGE FOR RECOVERY PURPOSES.    @@@@@@@H@@@@'MUDDLE' -       WORKS OUTSIDEXZ
)@@G@@ OF MAPPER; WORKS SIMILAR TO '@COPY' STATEMENT, @I@@@@                 EYA
)@@G@@XCEPT FOR OPTION MEANINGS.  HAS BEEN SUPPLIED ON RELEASE TAPE     @C@@@@YB
)@@G@@                 BUT WITHOUT DOCUMENTATION.     @@@@@@@I@@@@LIMITATIONS YC
)@@G@@ -   MAY ONLY OPERATE ON A RID (ELEMENT) AT A TIME. (NOT VERIFIED).     YD
)@@G@@@@@@@@@E@@@@EXAMPLE -        CREATE A NEW OCTAL TYPE WITHIN SAME FILE:  YE
)@@G@@@@@@@@@B@@@@                 @RUN  MUDDLE,UNIVAC,MAPER@B@@@@            YF
)@@G@@     @COPY,A  HLDMAP.MUDDLE,M @G@@@@                 @M,M  MAPER1.TYPE-0YG
)@@G@@302/RID-0,MAPER1.TYPE-0242/RID-0.   @^@@@@                 @EOF   @ @@@@YH
)@@G@@                 @PACK MAPER1.@@@@@@@H@@@@OPTIONS  -       A - DO NOT ERYI
)@@G@@ROR OFF, NO MATTER HOW SERIOUS THE AGGRAVATION  @G@@@@                 DYJ
)@@G@@ - PRODUCE A DUMP OF THE INPUT ELEMENT (FIELDATA)     @G@@@@            YK
)@@G@@     E - INHIBIT THE DISCARDING OF THE END OF REPORT IMAGE  @H@@@@      YL
)@@G@@           H - DO NOT DELETE HEADER LINES (ALSO DISABLES CHECKING FOR   YM
)@@G@@@A@@@@                     .DATE, ETC.)   @I@@@@                 L - PROYN
)@@G@@DUCE A LONG LISTING OF THE OUTPUT ELEMENT (132 COLUMNS)     @H@@@@      YO
)@@G@@           M - MAPPER TO MAPPER COPY (ANY OTHER ACTIVE OPTIONS IGNORED) YP
)@@G@@@B@@@@                 N - PRODUCE NO PRINTOUT  @F@@@@                 OYQ
)@@G@@ - PRODUCE AN OCTAL DUMP OF THE INPUT ELEMENT   @H@@@@                 PYR
)@@G@@ - ELEMENT IN QUESTION IS A PROGRAM, CONTAINING A PROCESSOR @I@@@@      YS
)@@G@@               CALL STATEMENT. TYPE OUTPUT ELEMENT ACCORDING TO PROCESSOYT
)@@G@@R.....@I@@@@                     THIS OPTION WORKS ONLY ON @ASM,@PDP(ASMYU
)@@G@@),AND @MAP SYMBOLICSSSSS@D@@@@                 Q - OUTPUT ELEMENT IS TO YV
)@@G@@BE IN ASCII @I@@@@                 S - PRODUCE A SHORT LISTING OF THE OUYW
)@@G@@TPUT ELEMENT (80 COLUMNS)     @H@@@@                 T - DO NOT TRANSLATYX
)@@G@@E TAB CODES TO SPACES.  IN THE PRESENCE OF@H@@@@                     THEYY
)@@G@@ 'Q' AND 'T' OPTIONS, TAB CODES WILL BECOME 'HT'.     @A@@@@            YZ
)@@G@@         (ASCII CTL)    @D@@@@                 X - ERROR OFF AT THE SLIGZA
)@@G@@HTEST EXCUSE@H@@@@                 Y - PROVIDE LINE SEQUENCE NUMBERS ON ZB
)@@G@@THE 'S' OR 'L' OPTION   @ @@@@                     LISTING. @H@@@@      ZC
)@@G@@           Z - IF USED IN CONJUNCTION WITH THE 'P' OPTION, WILL NAME THEZD
)@@G@@@H@@@@                     OUTPUT ELEMENT ACCORDING TO THE SI OR RO FIELZE
)@@G@@D ON THE    @H@@@@                     PROCESSOR CALL LINE IN THE REPORTZF
)@@G@@. IF NAMES ARE REPEATED,@H@@@@                     VERSION NAMES WILL BEZG
)@@G@@ ADDED, STARTING AT 'A' FOR THE     @B@@@@                     SECOND FIZH
)@@G@@ND, ETC.    @@@@@@@@@@@@@I@@@@PART 2 - READ/WRITE-RID & READ-MAPPER     ZI
)@@G@@                           (5 MINUTES)))))@@@@@@@H@@@@REASON FOR USE - IZJ
)@@G@@NTERFACE BATCH COBOL PROGRAMS TO MAPPER, ALLOWING ACCESS    @C@@@@      ZK
)@@G@@           TO MAPPER DATA FOR BATCH RUNS. @@@@@@@H@@@@'READ-RID' -     CZL
)@@G@@ONSISTS OF 3 SUBROUTINE CALLS; MROPEN, MRD & MRCLS; WHICH   @H@@@@      ZM
)@@G@@           OPEN A RID, READ A DATA LINE AND CLOSE A RID.  THE PACKET    ZN
)@@G@@@G@@@@                 DEFININITIONS SPECIFY THE FILE NAME, REPORT MODE,ZO
)@@G@@ ALPHA@G@@@@                 TYPE, AND RID.  TO USE, SET UP THE CONTROL ZP
)@@G@@PACKETS     @G@@@@                 IN THE WORKING-STORAGE SECTION OF THEZQ
)@@G@@ COBOL PROGRAM.   @@@@@@@@@@@@@B@@@@                 WORKING-STORAGE SECZR
)@@G@@TION. @A@@@@                 01  REPORT-PKT.    @F@@@@                  ZS
)@@G@@   05  PKT  PIC 9(10) COMP OCCURS 475 TIMES.    @A@@@@                 0ZT
)@@G@@1  REPORT-DEF.    @D@@@@                     05  REPORT-FILE        PIC ZU
)@@G@@X(12).@E@@@@                     05  REPORT-MODE        PIC 9(5) COMP.  ZV
)@@G@@@D@@@@                     05  FILLER             PIC XX.   @F@@@@      ZW
)@@G@@               05  REPORT-TYPE        PIC X.  (ALPHA TYPE)  @E@@@@      ZX
)@@G@@               05  REPORT-RID         PIC 9(5) COMP.  @B@@@@            ZY
)@@G@@     01  REPORT-INPUT-DATA.   @ @@@@                             .@C@@@@ZZ
)@@G@@                     (DEFINITION OF DATA LINE)  @ @@@@                  AA
)@@G@@           .@F@@@@                 01  END-OF-RID  REDEFINES REPORT-INPUAB
)@@G@@T-DATA.     @E@@@@                     05 FILLER          PIC 9(10) COMPAC
)@@G@@.     @D@@@@                     05 FILLER          PIC X(127).   @D@@@@AD
)@@G@@                     05 END-RID         PIC X(10).    @D@@@@            AE
)@@G@@         05 FILLER          PIC X(101).   @@@@@@@H@@@@                 TAF
)@@G@@HEN AS NEEDED, SETUP THE PACKETS WITH REQUIRED DATA AND     @F@@@@      AG
)@@G@@           CALL THE ROUTINE WITH THE CORRECT PACKET(S).     @@@@@@@ @@@@AH
)@@G@@                 OPEN-RID.    @F@@@@                     CALL 'MROPN' USAI
)@@G@@ING REPORT-DEF  REPORT-PKT.   @ @@@@                 READ-RID.    @G@@@@AJ
)@@G@@                     CALL 'MRD' USING REPORT-INPUT-DATA  REPORT-PRT.    AK
)@@G@@@F@@@@                     IF END-RID = 'END REPORT' GOTO CLOSE-RID.    AL
)@@G@@@B@@@@                               (MOVE DATA)@A@@@@                  AM
)@@G@@   GOTO READ-RID. @ @@@@                CLOSE-RID.    @D@@@@            AN
)@@G@@         CALL 'MRCLS' USING REPORT-PKT.   @@@@@@@@@@@@@H@@@@LIMITATIONS AO
)@@G@@-  READS ONLY FROM MAPER'N' FILES, NOT NECESSARILY CURRENT COPY   @G@@@@AP
)@@G@@               OF DATA.  HAS SOME PROBLEMS IF RIDS ARE OUT OF SEQUENCE. AQ
)@@G@@@B@@@@               (IE. AFTER MULTIPLE MERGES)@@@@@@@H@@@@WRITE-RID   AR
)@@G@@- THIS IS ANOTHER SUBROUTINE TO ALLOW ACCESS TO MAPPER DATA, ONLY @G@@@@AS
)@@G@@              THIS ONE ALLOWS WRITING OF A DATA RECORD IN MAPPER FORMAT,AT
)@@G@@@H@@@@              CREATING THE CONTROL ENVELOPE AROUND THE DATA AND ADAU
)@@G@@JUSTING     @F@@@@              THE REQUIRED POINTERS IN THE LINE ZERO IAV
)@@G@@NFORMATION. @H@@@@              (NOTE - AT THE TIME OF THIS WRITING, I DAW
)@@G@@O NOT KNOW OF ANY SITE  @G@@@@              ACTIVELY USING THIS SUBROUTIAX
)@@G@@NE, MOST USE A BOOMER,BOMBER, @H@@@@              BLASTER TYPE ROUTINE TAY
)@@G@@O CREATE A RID OR RIDS FROM AN SDF FILE   @B@@@@              RATHER THAAZ
)@@G@@N LINE AT A TIME) @@@@@@@H@@@@READ-MAPPER - THIS IS ANOTHER SUBROUTINE TBA
)@@G@@O ALLOW ACCESS TO MAPPER DATA, ONLY @H@@@@              THIS ONE LOCKS TBB
)@@G@@HE RID, COPIES OUT THE RID TO A SIDE FILE AND   @H@@@@              UNLOBC
)@@G@@CKS RID.  THUS, YOU GET THE MOST CURRENT COPY OF DATA IF    @H@@@@      BD
)@@G@@        IT BE IN MAPERN FILE OR IN MAPER0 (MUPERX).  CURRENTLY WORKS    BE
)@@G@@@H@@@@              ON FIELDATA ONLY, IT APPEARS TO BE EASILY UPGRADED TBF
)@@G@@O LVL 29,30 @H@@@@              BY CHANGING THE TYPE TABLE DEFNS.  THE UBG
)@@G@@SE OF ASCII DATA MAY    @H@@@@              REQUIRE A BIT MORE.  MODIFICBH
)@@G@@ATIONS ARE PARTIALLY SEEN THROUGH   @E@@@@              THE PROGRAM, BUTBI
)@@G@@ APPARENTLY NOT COMPLETED.    @@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@___IC 9(5) CBJ
)@@G@@OMP.  @B@@@@                 01  REPORT-INPUT-DATA.   @ @@@@            BK
